#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.60"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.60:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.60:0.2"
msgid "6. Upayavagga"
msgstr "6. Involvement"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.60:0.3"
msgid "60. Mahālisutta"
msgstr "60. With Mahāli"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.69"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn22.60:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "sn22.60:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho mahāli licchavi yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno "
"kho mahāli licchavi bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Mahāli the Licchavi went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:2.1"
msgid "“Pūraṇo, bhante, kassapo evamāha:"
msgstr "“Sir, Pūraṇa Kassapa says this:"

msgctxt "sn22.60:2.2"
msgid "‘natthi hetu natthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;"
msgstr "‘There is no cause or condition for the corruption of sentient beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:2.3"
msgid "ahetū appaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted without cause or reason."

msgctxt "sn22.60:2.4"
msgid "Natthi hetu natthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;"
msgstr "There’s no cause or condition for the purification of sentient beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:2.5"
msgid "ahetū appaccayā sattā visujjhantī’ti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified without cause or reason.’"

msgctxt "sn22.60:2.6"
msgid "Idha bhagavā kimāhā”ti?"
msgstr "What does the Buddha say about this?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:3.1"
msgid "“Atthi, mahāli, hetu atthi paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;"
msgstr ""
"“Mahāli, there is a cause and condition for the corruption of sentient "
"beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:3.2"
msgid "sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are corrupted with cause and reason."

msgctxt "sn22.60:3.3"
msgid "Atthi, mahāli, hetu, atthi paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;"
msgstr "There is a cause and condition for the purification of sentient beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:3.4"
msgid "sahetū sappaccayā sattā visujjhantī”ti."
msgstr "Sentient beings are purified with cause and reason.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:4.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, hetu katamo paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, what is the cause and condition for the corruption of sentient "
"beings?"

msgctxt "sn22.60:4.2"
msgid "kathaṃ sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissantī”ti?"
msgstr "How are sentient beings corrupted with cause and reason?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Rūpañca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantadukkhaṃ abhavissa dukkhānupatitaṃ "
"dukkhāvakkantaṃ anavakkantaṃ sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā rūpasmiṃ sārajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mahāli, if form were exclusively painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not "
"steeped in pleasure—sentient beings wouldn’t lust after it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:5.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, mahāli, rūpaṃ sukhaṃ sukhānupatitaṃ sukhāvakkantaṃ "
"anavakkantaṃ dukkhena, tasmā sattā rūpasmiṃ sārajjanti;"
msgstr ""
"But because form is pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and not "
"steeped in pain—sentient beings do lust after it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:5.3"
msgid "sārāgā saṃyujjanti; saṃyogā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""
"Since they lust after it, they’re caught up in it, and so they become "
"corrupted."

msgctxt "sn22.60:5.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, mahāli, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya;"
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for the corruption of sentient beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:5.5"
msgid "evaṃ sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr "This is how sentient beings are corrupted with cause and reason."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:6.1"
msgid ""
"Vedanā ca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantadukkhā abhavissa dukkhānupatitā "
"dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā vedanāya sārajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr "If feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.60:6.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, mahāli, vedanā sukhā sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā "
"dukkhena, tasmā sattā vedanāya sārajjanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:6.3"
msgid "sārāgā saṃyujjanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:6.4"
msgid "saṃyogā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:6.5"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahāli, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:6.6"
msgid "Evampi sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.70"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:7.1"
msgid "Saññā ca hidaṃ, mahāli … pe …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.60:7.2"
msgid ""
"saṅkhārā ca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantadukkhā abhavissaṃsu dukkhānupatitā "
"dukkhāvakkantā anavakkantā sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā saṅkhāresu sārajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.60:7.3"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, mahāli, saṅkhārā sukhā sukhānupatitā sukhāvakkantā anavakkantā "
"dukkhena, tasmā sattā saṅkhāresu sārajjanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:7.4"
msgid "sārāgā saṃyujjanti;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:7.5"
msgid "saṃyogā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:7.6"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahāli, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn22.60:7.7"
msgid "Evampi sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:8.1"
msgid ""
"Viññāṇañca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantadukkhaṃ abhavissa dukkhānupatitaṃ "
"dukkhāvakkantaṃ anavakkantaṃ sukhena, nayidaṃ sattā viññāṇasmiṃ sārajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness were exclusively painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not "
"steeped in pleasure—sentient beings wouldn’t lust after it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:8.2"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, mahāli, viññāṇaṃ sukhaṃ sukhānupatitaṃ sukhāvakkantaṃ "
"anavakkantaṃ dukkhena, tasmā sattā viññāṇasmiṃ sārajjanti;"
msgstr ""
"But because consciousness is pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure and "
"not steeped in pain—sentient beings do lust after it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:8.3"
msgid "sārāgā saṃyujjanti; saṃyogā saṅkilissanti."
msgstr ""
"Since they lust after it, they’re caught up in it, and so they become "
"corrupted."

msgctxt "sn22.60:8.4"
msgid "Ayampi kho, mahāli, hetu ayaṃ paccayo sattānaṃ saṅkilesāya."
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for the corruption of sentient beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:8.5"
msgid "Evampi sahetū sappaccayā sattā saṅkilissantī”ti."
msgstr "This is how sentient beings are corrupted with cause and reason.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:9.1"
msgid "“Katamo pana, bhante, hetu katamo paccayo sattānaṃ visuddhiyā;"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, what is the cause and condition for the purification of sentient "
"beings?"

msgctxt "sn22.60:9.2"
msgid "kathaṃ sahetū sappaccayā sattā visujjhantī”ti?"
msgstr "How are sentient beings purified with cause and reason?”"

msgctxt "sn22.60:9.3"
msgid ""
"“Rūpañca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantasukhaṃ abhavissa sukhānupatitaṃ sukhāvakkantaṃ "
"anavakkantaṃ dukkhena, nayidaṃ sattā rūpasmiṃ nibbindeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mahāli, if form were exclusively pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure "
"and not steeped in pain—sentient beings wouldn’t become disillusioned with "
"it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:9.4"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, mahāli, rūpaṃ dukkhaṃ dukkhānupatitaṃ dukkhāvakkantaṃ "
"anavakkantaṃ sukhena, tasmā sattā rūpasmiṃ nibbindanti;"
msgstr ""
"But because form is painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not steeped in "
"pleasure—sentient beings do become disillusioned with it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:9.5"
msgid "nibbindaṃ virajjanti; virāgā visujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned they become dispassionate, and so they are purified."

msgctxt "sn22.60:9.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, mahāli, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, sattānaṃ visuddhiyā."
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for the purification of sentient beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:9.7"
msgid "Evaṃ sahetū sappaccayā sattā visujjhanti."
msgstr "This is how sentient beings are purified with cause and reason."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli3.71"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.60:10.1"
msgid "Vedanā ca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantasukhā abhavissa … pe …"
msgstr "If feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.60:10.2"
msgid "saññā ca hidaṃ, mahāli … pe …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.60:10.3"
msgid "saṅkhārā ca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantasukhā abhavissaṃsu … pe …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.60:10.4"
msgid ""
"viññāṇañca hidaṃ, mahāli, ekantasukhaṃ abhavissa sukhānupatitaṃ "
"sukhāvakkantaṃ anavakkantaṃ dukkhena, nayidaṃ sattā viññāṇasmiṃ nibbindeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness were exclusively pleasurable—soaked and steeped in pleasure "
"and not steeped in pain—sentient beings wouldn’t become disillusioned with "
"it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:10.5"
msgid ""
"Yasmā ca kho, mahāli, viññāṇaṃ dukkhaṃ dukkhānupatitaṃ dukkhāvakkantaṃ "
"anavakkantaṃ sukhena, tasmā sattā viññāṇasmiṃ nibbindanti;"
msgstr ""
"But because consciousness is painful—soaked and steeped in pain and not "
"steeped in pleasure—sentient beings do become disillusioned with it."

msgctxt "sn22.60:10.6"
msgid "nibbindaṃ virajjanti; virāgā visujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned they become dispassionate, and so they are purified."

msgctxt "sn22.60:10.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, mahāli, hetu, ayaṃ paccayo, sattānaṃ visuddhiyā."
msgstr "This is a cause and condition for the purification of sentient beings."

msgctxt "sn22.60:10.8"
msgid "Evampi sahetū sappaccayā sattā visujjhantī”ti."
msgstr "This is how sentient beings are purified with cause and reason.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.60:10.9"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
